cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of deep learning models for regression and verification tasks suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of object-aware feature fusion and region proposal networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on tracking a moving object suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of online updates to adapt to appearance variations suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
